The European Investment Bank (EIB) isissuing a 40 billion yen eurobond due May 6, 1994 paying 4-5/8pct and priced at 101-1/2, lead Nomura International Ltd said.    The non-callable bond is available in denominations of onemln yen and will be listed in Luxembourg. The sellingconcession is 1-1/8 pct while management and underwritingcombined pays 1/2 pct. The payment date is May 6.    There is a mandatory purchase fund operating in years oneand two, except for the first month after the payment date,whereby the EIB can purchase up to five pct of the issue eachyear if it is trading below par. REUTER&#3;